{
  "texts": [
    "AgeThe effect of age on reading strategies is an area that deserves further study.",
    "As individuals grow older, their cognitive abilities, reading experiences, and reading purposes change.",
    "Younger people may focus more on the speed and breadth of information acquisition, while older people may focus more on comprehension and application of information.",
    "Therefore, different metacognitive reading strategies must be designed for different age groups to meet their reading needs and developmental characteristics.",
    "Gender differencesThe effect of gender on reading strategies is also a topic of great interest."
  ]
}